{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17625558","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17625558"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:26:19+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:26:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17033"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17033","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17033"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.64,0.04,0.24,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9723"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68328"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9723","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9723"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17033"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53786"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5146"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22875"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22879"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23029"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68328","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/68328"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EPancreatic enzyme replacement therapy contains lipase, amylase and protease to assist with digestion of dietary fats, carbohydrates and proteins.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following patients is most likely to require pancreatic enzyme replacement therapy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["A 65-year-old woman with lactose intolerance","A 25-year-old woman with cystic fibrosis","A 60-year-old man with gastro-oesophageal reflux disease","A 45-year-old man with coeliac disease","A 52-year-old woman with irritable bowel syndrome"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Epatient with cystic fibrosis\u003C/strong\u003E is most likely to require pancreatic enzyme replacement therapy. In cystic fibrosis, thick mucus secretions block pancreatic ducts, leading to exocrine pancreatic insufficiency. This results in poor digestion and malabsorption of nutrients.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other conditions do not typically cause pancreatic insufficiency:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELactose intolerance\u003C/strong\u003E occurs due to deficiency of the enzyme lactase in the small intestine brush border and does not involve pancreatic function.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGastro-oesophageal reflux disease\u003C/strong\u003E involves dysfunction of the lower oesophageal sphincter and has no effect on pancreatic enzyme production.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECoeliac disease\u003C/strong\u003E affects the small intestinal mucosa\u0027s ability to absorb nutrients but does not impair pancreatic enzyme secretion.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIrritable bowel syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E represents a functional gastrointestinal disorder that does not affect pancreatic enzyme production or secretion.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPancreatic enzyme replacement therapy helps patients with cystic fibrosis digest and absorb nutrients properly, preventing malnutrition and supporting growth and development.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Pancreatic enzyme replacement therapy is essential for patients with exocrine pancreatic insufficiency to aid digestion of fats, proteins and carbohydrates.","Cystic fibrosis commonly causes pancreatic insufficiency due to thick secretions blocking pancreatic ducts.","Other conditions requiring pancreatic enzyme replacement include chronic pancreatitis and pancreatic surgery."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53786"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17033"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53786","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53786"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-09T16:07:33+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-09T16:09:16+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9723"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68328"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:39:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","l